# Phase 19 — Cloudflare Disaster Recovery Governance

## Objective

Add disaster recovery tabletop exercise templates, recovery ownership assignments, restore evidence requirements, and a manual recovery checklist for Cloudflare runtime failures within the ZeaZ Platform. This phase establishes the human-in-the-loop DR governance layer.

This phase must NOT deploy, apply, destroy, or mutate Cloudflare. It is a documentation-only governance layer.

---

## Branch Name

```
fix/cloudflare-disaster-recovery-governance
```

## Commit Message

```
docs(cloudflare): add disaster recovery governance
```

---

## Scope

- Create DR governance overview doc
- Create tabletop exercise template
- Create manual recovery checklist (read-only, no destructive commands)
- Create restore evidence template
- Create recovery ownership matrix
- Update `infra/cloudflare/README.md` with Phase 19 entry
- All content must be human-executable (no automated destructive actions)

---

## Non-Goals

- Do NOT include executable commands that mutate Cloudflare
- Do NOT run `wrangler deploy`, `terraform apply`, `tofu apply`, or any Cloudflare write
- Do NOT print, log, or commit any secrets or credentials
- Do NOT start or restart any services
- Do NOT edit `/etc/cloudflared/config.yml`
- Do NOT modify files outside Phase 19 scope
- The checklist must remain read-only / manual — it documents human steps, not automation

---

## Safety Rules

1. All recovery steps must be clearly labeled as MANUAL — requiring human decision before execution
2. Never include destructive commands (DELETE, DROP, DESTROY, purge) without explicit WARNING labels and MANUAL tags
3. Never print credentials, tokens, or tunnel IDs in examples
4. All docs must clearly separate: scenario description | impact | detection | recovery steps | evidence required
5. DR templates must use sanitized placeholder values in all examples
6. Active credential file must NEVER be printed or committed

---

