## Suggested Commands

```bash
# Create branch
git checkout -b fix/cloudflare-disaster-recovery-governance

# After writing files, verify
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-disaster-recovery-governance.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-dr-tabletop-template.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-manual-recovery-checklist.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-restore-evidence-template.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-recovery-ownership-matrix.md

# Verify all steps labeled MANUAL or READ-ONLY
grep -c "\[MANUAL\]\|\[READ-ONLY" docs/infra/cloudflare-manual-recovery-checklist.md

# Secret check
grep -RInE '(token|secret|password|credential|api[_-]?key)' \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-disaster-recovery-governance.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-dr-tabletop-template.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-manual-recovery-checklist.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-restore-evidence-template.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-recovery-ownership-matrix.md || echo "No secrets found"

# Git status
git diff --name-only

# Commit
git add docs/infra/cloudflare-disaster-recovery-governance.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-dr-tabletop-template.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-manual-recovery-checklist.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-restore-evidence-template.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-recovery-ownership-matrix.md \
        infra/cloudflare/README.md
git commit -m "docs(cloudflare): add disaster recovery governance"

git push origin fix/cloudflare-disaster-recovery-governance
gh pr create --title "docs(cloudflare): add disaster recovery governance" \
  --body "Phase 19: Adds DR tabletop template, manual recovery checklist, restore evidence template, and recovery ownership matrix for 8 DR scenarios. Read-only governance. No deploy. No secrets."
```

